definition: the 64 hexagrams of the Book of Changes (I Ching or Yi Jing) 易經|易经

sentences.english: Now, more than 60 percent of kindergarteners attend for a full day.
sentences.chinese: 而现在，超过百分之六十的幼儿参加了全托。

sentences.english: I scanned the sixty faces in my economics class at UNLV.
sentences.chinese: 我扫视了一下全班六十张脸。

sentences.english: Sixty percent of the examinee were very satisfied.
sentences.chinese: 百分之六十的考生都非常的满意。

sentences.english: But the Democrats have lost their sixtieth vote.
sentences.chinese: 但是，民主党人丧失了其第六十票。

sentences.english: Sixty-three students participated in this contest.
sentences.chinese: 本学期背诵比赛共有六十三位同学参加。

sentences.english: Chinese Hamsters were introduced into the UK pet market in the 1960s.
sentences.chinese: 二十世纪六十年代被引进到英国宠物市场。

sentences.english: Plateaus and mountains make up 60 per cent of China's total area.
sentences.chinese: 高原和山地占中国总面积的百分之六十。

sentences.english: Now in her mid-60s, she runs at least 2 miles every day.
sentences.chinese: 如今她六十多岁，每天至少跑两英里。

sentences.english: The exercises are numbered from 1 to 365.
sentences.chinese: 练习从一至三百六十五逐一编号。

sentences.english: Something happened in the late 1950s and early ’60s.
sentences.chinese: 五十年代末六十年代初有不少这种事。

sentences.english: All the multitude as it were one man, forty-two thousand three hundred sixty.
sentences.chinese: 全会众共计四万二千三百六十人。

sentences.english: Article 164 The easement may not be transferred alone.
sentences.chinese: 第一百六十四条地役权不得单独转让。

sentences.english: My daughter learned half of the content of lesson 65 this evening.
sentences.chinese: 今天晚上，我女儿学习了第六十五课的一半内容。

sentences.english: Article 169. An independent director may submit his resignation before the expiration of his term.
sentences.chinese: 第一百六十九条独立董事在任期届满钱可以提出辞职。

sentences.english: Article 67 The creditors' meeting may decide to establish a creditors' committee.
sentences.chinese: 第六十七条债权人会议可以决定设立债权人委员会。
